 is either this pre-existing halo medium, which has been swept-up and\nshock heated by the starburst-driven wind, or wind material compressed near the\nwalls of the outflow by reverse shocks within the wind. In either case the\nX-ray emission provides us with a powerful probe of the properties of gaseous\nhalos around star-forming disk galaxies.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Fri, 27 Jun 2003 17:17:19 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Wed, 14 Jan 2004 18:21:18 GMT"}],"update_date":"2009-11-10"}
